{
  "texts": [
    "With appropriate permissions, agents can collaborate with SLPs by providing context-aware inputs and minimizing cognitive burden (Roose, 2025).",
    "Agents are designed to iteratively request context before producing tailored outputs.",
    "Multiple agents can coordinate with one another-for instance, a screening agent may communicate with referral, scheduling, and billing agents to streamline workflows.",
    "Specialized agents may offer more practical value than general-purpose LLMs in many SLP contexts (Hao, 2025).",
    "Using an apt agent, the author easily developed useful codes for a single purpose (see examples in Rami, 2025a Rami,, 2025b Rami,, 2025c))."
  ]
}